Body: can you give me an example of a token that is valued at that price ( 0.00000001 )? I don't think that is possible because it means they will need a huge amount of tokens in order to have a portion they can sell for funding and they will generate a huge amount of token supply.  Let me give you a computation. If a token is valued at 0.00000001 that means there will be 100millions of token in 1ETH. 0.00000001  x 100,000,000 If a project need a funding of 10M USD from Private/Public  ICO and and allocate  50% of total token then their total token supply should be around 10 Trillion, with that amount of supply no one will be interested to invest.  10M USD = 50k ETH @ 200USD/ETH 50k ETH = 5 Trillion (50% of total supply allocated for ICOs) 10Trillion = Total Token Supply  so @ 1 ETH = 16 700 ICH ICO rate, it is one of the cheapest price out there.
